Example Run
-----------

{% if ex and ex.inputs %}
Running the Python code with the following input{% if ex.inputs | length > 1 %}s{% endif %}:

.. code-block:: text

    python {{ example_name }}.py {% for img in ex.inputs %}{{ img }} {% endfor %}{% if has_output %}/tmp/{{ example_name }}_output.nrrd{% endif %}

{% endif %}

.. exec_code::
    :hide_output:

    # --- hide: start ---
    from pathlib import Path
    from example_utils import run_example, save_image
    data_path = Path("${SimpleITK_DATA_ROOT}")
    args = [
        '',
        {{ ns.run_args }}
    ]
    args = [str(a) for a in args]
    return_dict = run_example('{{ example_name }}', 'main', args)
    for key, value in return_dict.items():
        save_image(value, f"{{ example_name }}_{key}")
    # --- hide: stop ---

